    <p>For the complete melatonin gummy rankings across all dose levels, see our <a href="/best-melatonin-gummies/">best melatonin gummies</a> guide. For children's melatonin specifically, read our <a href="/sleep/melatonin-gummies-for-kids/">melatonin gummies for kids</a> guide.</p>

    <!-- VERDICT -->
    <div class="verdict">
      <h3>The Bottom Line on Melatonin Dosing</h3>
      <p><strong>Start low:</strong> 0.5-1mg for most adults. The physiological dose (0.3mg) is often sufficient. Higher doses do not produce proportionally better sleep.</p>
      <p><strong>Timing matters more than dose:</strong> Take melatonin 30-60 minutes before your desired bedtime. For circadian phase shifting, take it 3-5 hours before your current natural sleep time.</p>
      <p><strong>Less is more:</strong> If your current 5mg or 10mg gummy causes grogginess, try halving or quartering it. Many people sleep better at 1mg than 10mg.</p>
      <p><strong>Address the root cause:</strong> Melatonin is a signal, not a sedative. Combine it with proper sleep hygiene — consistent schedule, no screens before bed, cool dark room — for best results.</p>
    </div>

